{"TopicId":190539,"ForumId":39,"TopicTitle":"(Kinda) Turn Based Kerbal War","CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-21T20:37:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-21T20:37:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003ETBKW\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E(Turn-Based Kerbal War)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003ECreated by Mieyo\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EThe idea started a while ago, let\u2019s say three months back in the past. It was a turn-based wargame using my favorite version of KSP, 1.3.1. I played it with my friend and we had a blast. But why is it so fun? Probably cause it\u2019s so simple, it may not be as large scale as I want it to be but the 1v1 idea is really interesting. The game is all ran through KSP 1.3 and a messaging platform of your choice (Discord, Gmail, etc) this is all done through downloaded quicksaves and a lot of effort in the setup of the game at the start. It\u2019s mostly stock I\u0027m\u00A0adding BD Armory and Hyperedit into the mix I feel like this will make it a lot more fun! And since it\u2019s mostly stock that\u2019ll make people wanna build better ships with more brains than brawn. (Gameplay example below)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EHere\u2019s a good example of a small bombing run in case you\u2019re confused about how it works:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003ELet\u2019s say I built a small airforce base on the western side of the Mun, but you built one very close to mine. So I decide to attack you with one of my many space bombers. So I attack you, blow up your base and land back at my base, this is a total of 3 turns, you get a max of 5. After I do all of this, I quicksave the whole thing send it to you and laugh at how awesome my bombing run was. Then, you counter-attack (or something) send that quicksave to me and then we keep going until someone surrenders or I kill all your Kerbals.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EThat\u2019s the basics! (for now) Below I will post open spots and other do-dads that are important to the game. Please feel free to send me a message if you have any questions that are relevant to the game itself. I hope y\u2019all have a wonderful day/night! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EOpen Spots:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EMieyo\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003ELapis\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003EArco123\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003ECapitalist Kerbal\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EPlanets legal to battle on:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EKerbin\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EMun\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EMinmus\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EPoint system:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E1 point for destroying a small air/ground unit\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E2 points for bombing and destroying a small air/ground base\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E3 points for obliterating a medium air/ground unit\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E4 points for clapping a medium air/ground base\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E15 points for clapping out of anything bigger than 200 parts\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E(Whoever has the most points at the end of a battle wins)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-28T01:29:38Z\u0022 title=\u002212/28/2019 01:29  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 28, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Mieyo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdding things\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-24T05:28:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about bd armory. If that\u0027s in there prepare to die and I would like to join anyways.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-24T18:56:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you so much for replying to my post! Really appreciate it! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EI\u0027ll see what I can do with BD Armory, I might add it actually I\u0027ve been thinking about it for a while, I\u0027ll edit the post soon so I can update the rules. So glad you are willing to join! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lapis","CreatedById":193784,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-24T19:23:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am kinda interested in this, i would like to participate if you have room. try to keep it from roleplay though, as that would violate forum rules.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-24T19:24:21Z\u0022 title=\u002212/24/2019 07:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 24, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Lapis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-24T19:27:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe always have room! It is a 1v1 type battle if that effects anything you want to do.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you want me to put in a spot?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lapis","CreatedById":193784,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-24T19:29:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure, there was a topic somewhere similar to this but with rockets, i recall\u00A0 \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/165701-sidestrafe2462/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022165701\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/165701-sidestrafe2462/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sidestrafe2462\u003C/a\u003E and\u00A0 \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/95108-panzer1b/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002295108\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/95108-panzer1b/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@panzer1b\u003C/a\u003E being\u00A0 prominent members.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-24T20:05:10Z\u0022 title=\u002212/24/2019 08:05  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 24, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Lapis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Epinged the wrong people\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-24T19:31:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, I\u0027ll take a look at that.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll also put you in a blank spot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-25T01:16:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would love to play anyways. I build great god of rod weapons.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-25T06:25:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome! I\u0027ll put you in! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Holoday","CreatedById":201990,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-26T14:00:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan I join? This sounds fun.\u00A0Do I need to share discord?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-27T00:39:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes! You can join! If you want, you can PM me your discord. I don\u0027t have the\u00A0server setup yet\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-01-02T19:08:59Z\u0022 title=\u002201/02/2020 07:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 2, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Mieyo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Holoday","CreatedById":201990,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-27T05:24:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMieyo it\u2019s DirtyPenguin #8837\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-27T15:26:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey Dirty! Have you seen my thing yet? This is the thing we were talking about but on the forums!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-27T15:37:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, use 1.8 but with tweakscale, Bd armory and that\u0027s it. But, why don\u0027t we download the multiplayer mod DMP?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Holoday","CreatedById":201990,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-27T21:38:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223721526\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190539\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221577460368\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Arco123\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Arco123 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey Dirty! Have you seen my thing yet? This is the thing we were talking about but on the forums!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes... didn\u0027t see a video link there though?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yeet_TheDinosaur","CreatedById":197265,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-28T00:41:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223721529\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190539\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221577461032\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Arco123\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Arco123 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, use 1.8 but with tweakscale, Bd armory and that\u0027s it. But, why don\u0027t we download the multiplayer mod DMP?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a great idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-28T01:25:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it ok if we keep with 1.3.1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-28T01:34:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223721595\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190539\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221577482697\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201990\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Capitalist Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Capitalist Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes... didn\u0027t see a video link there though?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGo down and it should be there below the main posts...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-02T19:06:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, here\u0027s an update about the whole situation.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst, I will not be able to host a DMP server for the war itself. However, if anyone is able to host it that would be great. Second, I would love to use BDarmory however, I would prefer it to be stock but it really depends how you all feel about it. Third, we are going to keep this war in KSP 1.3.1 just because I\u0027m running everything on my itty-bitty chromebook and the newer versions of KSP absolutely fry my poor chromebook. (Poor chromebook)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOverview:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP 1.3.1 will be the version we are using\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDMP and BDarmory is optional and will be implemented with a vote\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBonus:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m almost done setting up the Discord server so stay tuned! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lapis","CreatedById":193784,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-02T23:14:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@mieyo we can take an action(e.g. firing a weapon) then pass the save to the other person instead of using dmp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-03T00:32:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223723860\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190539\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221578006868\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022193784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lapis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Lapis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@mieyo we can take an action(e.g. firing a weapon) then pass the save to the other person instead of using dmp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, that\u0027ll work a lot better. Thanks Lapis! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-03T03:25:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t guarantee I will be able to participate, but if I can I would like to. Real life has been all over the place recently though so I can\u0027t say for sure I want to do this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would like some clarification on somethings though:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nWhat exactly constitutes a turn? I see there is a 5 turn limit per turn limit. With the examples given there is a lot of grey area into how much you can do each turn, I\u0027d suggest making a list.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nMods list and version. This is VERY important to lay down, and to keep as simple as possible. If it\u0027s not set in stone then we will have compatibility issues, and if the modlist is not simple it may discourage people, and it could get frustrating.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIs there a win condition? If not this will likely end with people getting bored and dropping out.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nAdditionally we need a surefire way to keep roleplay off of the forums. This means no nation building beyond maybe a simple flag (I suggest only using in game flags because if we used custom ones we\u0027d have to share flags to each other and that can be confusing for those who haven\u0027t done it before). The mods tend to get uneasy about roleplay as it often results in fighting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso I like the Discord idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mieyo","CreatedById":193573,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-03T04:40:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew update thingy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EMods allowed:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EHyperedit\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003ETweak scale\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EMechjeb\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EWhat a turn can be consisted of:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EFiring a weapon (Small missiles 3 times, medium missiles 2 times, and large missiles 1 time)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EMoving to the target. Max movement of 3 of the 5 actions listed (Orbit, suborbit, landing, moving on the ground 10 KM, and moving through the air 20 KM)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003ESetting up something, note this ends your whole turn (Setting up an ambush, building a base ETC)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EBonus stuff:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EAll these can be repeated to make a total of 5 turns inside of one turn. Also, hyperedit can be used to set up bases, fighters in a space battle or even supply runs. You cannot hyperedit closer to an enemy but you can hyperedit up to 25 meters to an enemy base. You can however hyperedit to rondevu to an enemy up to 50 meters away but you must manually get closer to them. This means you can hyperedit anywhere except to get closer to an enemy that you are already within range of.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Dressian Exploder","CreatedById":191542,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-03T07:36:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere have been many attempts at doing turn-based Kerbal \u0027War\u0027. My only advice is probably have a look at the examples set by the endless clash between TAPE gaming and TheBeardyPenguin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lapis","CreatedById":193784,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-03T16:03:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/193573-mieyo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022193573\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/193573-mieyo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Mieyo\u003C/a\u003E How about aircraft turns are defined by its features. Meaning you take off from point A and you can bomb point B point B has to be within range of the aircraft, say: 30% of its fuel payload and\u00A0 then it returns to base.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}